{
  "texts": [
    "A single finding was obtained for each region to construct a more homogenous dataset to simulate the detection performance for cribriform patterns.",
    "A patch image was considered positive for the cribriform pattern when at least 50% of the patch image was positive.",
    "As a negative control, we considered a total of 836 patients with Gleason patterns 3 to 5, with the exception of patients with Gleason pattern 4 and cribriform patterns.",
    "These images for the negative control originated from the previous test conditions for GS detection.",
    "For the cribriform pattern, we measured the detection accuracy and the interrater agreement between the pathologist and the DL model."
  ]
}